Lady Hawk decided to let the reptile win. &quot;OK, you win, I&#39;m no match for the
mighty serpent, You have had the last word so I&#39;ll just give up and sit here
silently.&quot; She was tired and fed up with the tiresome reparte that the two
were emitting. She didn&#39;t want to hear another word from the annoying snake.
Even though he did claim to have royal blood and did seem to have some need
for them to act like a married couple.

The shuttle shook as it landed. &quot;Thank the Avatars of the wind.&quot; (Her form
of religion) She was glad to have finally landed. Now maybe she could
finally be rid of this annoying creature. &quot;Now can He let go?&quot; she asked ouy
of annoyance. A snake that large was cramping her wrapped arm and wings. She
wanted to return to robot mode and a more dignified form.(She&#39;s been stuck
in half hawk mode since the battle at the old base.) She used her middle eye
to scan the surroundings. She was sure precautions would be taken so she&#39;d
wait for a more opportune moment to escape. Or maybe Zardus would accept her
mistake and let her continue her work. It benefitted the alliance to much to
be left alone and Squizzy didn&#39;t know enough to continue.

Najah opened his big mouth once more questioning her intelligence.

Lady Hawk looked straight at Zardus, he was getting cocky. He didn&#39;t think
she could do any damage while she was wrapped up. He was wrong. If she were
to open her mouth and shriek right now the Alliance would be looking for a
new leader. Unfortunately that also meant that Veratis would be looking for
a new daughter.

&quot;What exactly is it you&#39;d like to know?&quot; she asked knowing he heald all the
cards. She had to run a bluff and hope to cut her losses. &quot;Have the
invertabrate release me and I&#39;ll tell you everything.&quot;

